-- China Car Accident Kills 11 Children in Jiangxi, Radio Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-12-24T11:05:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-24/china-car-accident-kills-11-children-in-jiangxi-radio-reports.html
A car accident in eastern  China ’s
Jiangxi province killed 11 children, China National Radio
reported today.  The van in which the children were riding fell into a pond
this morning, the state broadcaster reported. Three children
died at the scene, while another eight died after medical
efforts failed, according to the report. A total of 16 people
were riding in the van at the time of the accident, China
National Radio reported.  A reason for why the van fell into the pond and ages for
the children killed weren’t given. The official Xinhua News
Agency earlier today reported that the van was carrying
kindergarten children.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
